#      easy-auto-multiple-choice              #
#                                             #
###############################################

A minimal auto-multiple-choice CLI/GUI

Install :
---------

To use easy-auto-multiple-choice you need to install
auto-multiple-choice, pdftk and imagemagick.
https://www.auto-multiple-choice.net

So just install these packages and copy the 
easy-auto-multiple-choice script in your binary 
directory (usually /usr/bin, don't forget to
chmod +x it).


Usage :
-------

To launch the GUI just run the script with the "gui"
parameter :

easy-auto-multiple-choice gui


Here the complete CLI/GUI usage :

usage : easy-auto-multiple-choice [working_path] <action>
Possible actions are :
   gui          : launch the GUI
   set-students : read student list from CSV file
   edit-test    : launch the test editor
   build-test   : build a printable test
   read-copies  : read copies from scans
   clean        : clean all files except test source and student list
